            "rows": 6,
            "default_value": "Port St Mary Commissioners are the local authority for the village of Port St Mary on the Isle of Man.\r\nThe Board of Port St Mary Commissioners has represented the Village District of Port St Mary since its formation in 1890. The Board consists of seven members who are elected by public vote every four years, with the next election due in 2029.\r\nPort St Mary Commissioners deliver essential local services including refuse collection, housing, beach cleaning, street lighting, and the maintenance of public spaces and facilities throughout the village.",
